two of the sample config files are marked executable.

do you want to include the git chmod or would you prefer a separate commit?

based on Yocto documentation https://docs.yoctoproject.org/dev/ref-manual/features.html#image-features "allow-root-login "allow-root-login feature in Yocto allows SSH root logins, but it does not automatically set the root password to be blank. To make an image suitable for development with SSH root access and a blank password, need to combine allow-root-login with the empty-root-password feature."
presumably this file doesn't need to be executable.
